</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-24_ pf-text-1">Anaphylaxis affects approximately 1-2% of the global population, with the incidence rising recently.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-26_ pf-text-1">According to the European Academy of Allergy and Clinical Immunology, food-induced anaphylaxis accounts for the majority of cases, with common triggers including peanuts, tree nuts, shellfish, and dairy.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-28_ pf-text-1">The severity of anaphylactic reactions can vary, ranging from mild symptoms to rapid and life-threatening complications, such as airway obstruction and cardiovascular collapse.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-30_ pf-text-1">Prompt administration of epinephrine (adrenaline) is the cornerstone of anaphylaxis management, emphasising the critical importance of preparedness and awareness.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-32_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Key definitions</span></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Anaphylaxis</strong> - An acute, severe allergic reaction that can involve multiple organ systems and progresses rapidly, posing an immediate threat to life.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Epinephrine (Adrenaline)</strong> - A hormone and medication used to treat severe allergic reactions by constricting blood vessels, relaxing airway muscles, and increasing heart rate.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-41_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">Causes of anaphylaxis</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-45_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Anaphylaxis can be triggered by various allergens, including foods, insect stings, medications, and latex. Upon exposure to an allergen, the immune system overreacts, releasing a surge of chemicals, such as histamine, which leads to widespread inflammation and symptoms.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-47_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-48_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3">Risk factors
</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Individuals with a history of allergies, asthma, or previous anaphylactic episodes are at an increased risk. Additionally, certain factors, such as age, genetics, and environmental exposures, can influence susceptibility to anaphylaxis.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-53_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-54_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3">Anaphylaxis symptoms
</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The symptoms of anaphylaxis can manifest within seconds to minutes after exposure to an allergen and may include:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-59_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-60_ pf-text-1">Difficulty breathing
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-62_ pf-text-1">Swelling of the face, throat, or tongue</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-64_ pf-text-1">Rapid heartbeat
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-66_ pf-text-1">Dizziness or loss of consciousness
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-68_ pf-text-1">Nausea, vomiting, or abdominal pain.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-70_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-71_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-72_ pf-heading-1-h3">Treatment and prevention
</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-74_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Immediate administration of epinephrine is paramount in managing anaphylaxis. Other supportive measures, such as supplemental oxygen, intravenous fluids, and antihistamines, may also be necessary to stabilise the patient and alleviate symptoms. Following an episode of anaphylaxis, individuals should seek medical evaluation to prevent future occurrences and develop an action plan for emergency response.
<br><br>Preventing anaphylaxis involves identifying and avoiding known triggers, carrying emergency medication (e.g., epinephrine auto-injectors), and educating oneself and others about the condition. In addition, healthcare providers play a crucial role in the timely diagnosis and management of allergies, empowering patients with the knowledge and resources needed to minimise the risk of anaphylactic reactions.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-76_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-77_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-78_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-80_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-81_ pf-text-1">Educate yourself and others about anaphylaxis, its triggers, and the appropriate response.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-83_ pf-text-1">Ensure access to emergency medication, such as epinephrine auto-injectors, in case of accidental exposure.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-85_ pf-text-1">Develop a personalised anaphylaxis action plan in collaboration with your healthcare provider.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-87_ pf-text-1">Advocate for allergen labeling and increased awareness in public settings, such as restaurants and schools.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-89_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-90_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-91_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
